               <p>PHILIP HARDWICK. I am an <rs id="t18320906-202-viclabel1136" type="occupation">architect</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-202-victim1689 t18320906-202-viclabel1136"></join>, and live in Russell-square. On the 11th of July, about nine o'clock in the morning, I was in <placeName id="t18320906-202-crimeloc1137">Fleet-street, near Bridge-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18320906-202-crimeloc1137" type="placeName" value="Fleet-street, near Bridge-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18320906-202-crimeloc1137" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-202-off1134 t18320906-202-crimeloc1137"></join>, and felt a pressure, and my pocket was lighter than before; I turned round, and found the prisoner close at my elbow - he appeared alone; nobody but him was near enough to take my handkerchief - I collared, and gave him in charge; I saw my handkerchief about a yard from him, laying in the carriage-road - I saw it taken up; he asked what I meant by collaring him, and denied the charge: Mr. Hudson was with me.</p>
               <p>MR. HUDSON. I am a Prothonatary of the Court of Common Pleas. I was with Mr. Hardwick, who seized the prisoner, and crossed the road - I saw the prisoner at that instant throw the handkerchief down, which I took up and gave to Mr. Hardwick.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320906-202-person1690">
                  WILLIAM 
                  ELMES
               <interp inst="t18320906-202-person1690" type="surname" value="ELMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-202-person1690" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320906-202-person1690" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. The prisoner was brougth to the watch-house with this handkerchief.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. For him to say nobody was near me is false; there were a number of people passing at the time I was.</p>
               <p>
